President Mauricio Macri of Argentina welcomes President Donald Trump to Argentina on his first visit to Latin America and his first time in Argentina. Macri expresses gratitude for the support received from the United States, especially during difficult times and in dealing with the International Monetary Fund. He also highlights the collaboration between the two countries in areas such as education, defense, and domestic security. Macri emphasizes the importance of U.S. investments in Argentina and the significant number of American tourists visiting the country. President Trump reciprocates the friendship and reminisces about his past business dealings with Macri's family. They discuss various topics, including trade and military purchases, during their meeting. Trump commends Macri for his leadership and job performance.